FBIS3-43571 "drafr006_b_94006" FBIS-AFR-94-006 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Jan 1994 EAST AFRICA Kenya Minister To Issue Statement EA0701172694 Nairobi KNA in English 1345 GMT 7 Jan 94 EA0701172694 Nairobi KNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Nairobi 7 Jan (KNA) -- The minister for tourism and wildlife Mr. Noah Katana Ngala has promised to issue a ministerial statement on the ongoing Leakey saga. Speaking in his office during a courtesy call by the Indian minister for civil aviation and tourism Mr. Ghulam Nabi Azad Mr. Ngala said the ministry is assessing the situation and will respond soon. [sentence as received] Twenty-five local authorities in the country have called for Dr. Richard Leakey's dismissal as the director of Kenya Wildlife Services. They accused him of refusing to remit 25 percent of total collections to the councils, as directed by the government. [passage omitted]
